# QR Code Visitor Check-in System - Environment Variables

# Zapier Webhook URLs
# ====================

# Webhook URL for QR code generation (sends visitor data + QR code to automation)
# This webhook should trigger when a new QR code is created for a visitor
# Example: https://hooks.zapier.com/hooks/catch/123456/abcdef/
NEXT_PUBLIC_ZAPIER_QR_WEBHOOK_URL=your_zapier_qr_webhook_url_here

# Webhook URL for visitor check-in (sends check-in notification to automation)
# This webhook should trigger when a visitor is checked in via QR scan
# Example: https://hooks.zapier.com/hooks/catch/123456/ghijkl/
NEXT_PUBLIC_ZAPIER_CHECKIN_WEBHOOK_URL=your_zapier_checkin_webhook_url_here

# Instructions:
# =============
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Replace the example URLs with your actual Zapier webhook URLs
# 3. Make sure to use NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix for client-side access
# 4. Set up your Zapier workflows to handle the webhook data
#
# QR Generation Webhook Data:
# - visitorName, visitorCompany, visitorEmail, purpose, hostEmail
# - qrCodeDataUrl (base64 image), qrCodeData (JSON string)
# - createdAt, visitorId, timestamp, action: 'qr_code_generated'
#
# Check-in Webhook Data:
# - visitorName, visitorCompany, visitorEmail, purpose, hostEmail
# - checkedInAt, checkedInTime, identificationNotes, locationNotes
# - visitorId, timestamp, action: 'visitor_checked_in'
